# Shell scripts must always use LF line endings — they are executed inside
# Linux containers (Docker). CRLF line endings break the shebang line
# ("/bin/sh^M": bad interpreter) and can break `set -e`/command parsing.
# Without this, Windows checkouts with core.autocrlf=true would silently
# convert these files to CRLF and crash the nginx-https container at startup
# (Rule 3 — blocking issue, found while adding the first .sh file to this repo).
*.sh text eol=lf
